The Wynn Resorts project in Ras Al Khaimah, UAE, has been appointed a design consultant by Marjan, the leading master developer for freehold land in the Emirate of Ras Al Khaimah, in partnership with RAK Hospitality Holding (RAKHH), an integrated hospitality asset owner and manager, and Wynn Resorts, an American developer and operator of high end hotels and casinos. HKS, an international design firm with more than 1,400 architects, interior designers, urban designers, scientists, artists, anthropologists and more, is the apointee. The Wynn Resorts Project is developed under the Ras Al-Khaimah-based master developer of freehold properties in the United Arab Emirates. It is set to be located on Al Marjan Island, a group of 4 coral-shaped islands in a man-made archipelago located in Ras al-Khaimah. in the Persian Gulf. Also Read: Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse Construction in Ajman, UAE, Begins Featuring an integrated resort that will be accompanied by gaming and entertainment amenities as well as a world-class hotel, the Wynn Resort Project in Ras Al Khaimah will be the first of its kind within the MENA region by Wynn Resorts. It will also be a global first for the US-listed developer and luxury resort operator. It is expected to open in 2026 upon which wil play a significant role in the tourism sector of Ras Al Khaimah. While commenting on the appointment of a design consultant for the project, the Chief Executive Officer of Marjan, Eng Abdulla Abdooli explained that the project aims to offer guests exceptional dining and entertainment as well as accommodations, in a spectacular setting. He also happily expressed excitement over realizing the company’s vision for the project on the island while working with HKS Architects, and concluded by stating that the company aims to raise the benchmark in luxury hospitality in the Middle East as well as boost tourism in the country and attract visitors from all across the world.